tips to help stay awake i am currently studying for my exams and i realise that i keep feeling really tired despite having slept about hours and even napping in the middle of the day here's the thing i can't drink coffee i have tried it numerous times and instead of waking me up i feel even more tired as compared to before i drunk it so coffee's out does anyone have any tips on how to reduce fatigue or to help me stay awake and alert thanks there are two really good ways to stay awake eat something more specifically something that has carbs and protein your body will burn the carbs turning them into energy and the protein will help to prevent you from feeling a low once the carbs are all burned up take a power nap it could really help boost your energy however don't nap for more than about minutes or you could wake up feeling really cranky Sleep Atkins Nutritional Approach Narcolepsy Siesta Polyphasic sleep Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Dieting Bodybuilding Bong Lucid dreaming Insomnia Prostate cancer Weight training Milk Carburetor Energy drink Hypoglycemia Opportunity rover timeline for 2004 March Opportunity rover timeline for 2004 February Apollo 8 Wind turbine Caffeine Drowning Marathon (sport) Word of Wisdom Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Coffee Toyota Prius Mattress Traumatic brain injury Out-of-body experience Cannabis (drug) Sonic the Hedgehog Toyota Corolla Urinary incontinence Blitzball Chronic fatigue syndrome Fertility awareness Nutrition STS-62 Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March Singlish Fecal incontinence Turbocharger Food Yerba mate Chocolate Equine conformation Episodes of Lost (Season 1) South Beach diet Dream The Life and Times of Juniper Lee Sleep apnea Cocaine First aid Futurama (TV series - season 5) Dog Modafinil Everwood Protein Fasting Shaggy dog story The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Energy development Cybertron Common cold Hide and Seek (Stargate Atlantis) Anemia Social rule Oh My Goddess! Survival skills Veganism Chicken Dialysis